Product Version     25.10    Cadence Design Systems, Inc.
create_buffer_psPM_table(25.10)                create_buffer_psPM_table(25.10)

Name
       create_buffer_psPM_table

Syntax
       create_buffer_psPM_table

       [-help]

       [-buffers <string>]

       [-file <string>]

       [-inverters <string>]

       [-layer <string>]

       -max_target_slew <float>-min_target_slew <float>[-rpt_file <string>]

       [-slew_interval <float>]

       Automatically  calculates how much distance a specified list of buffers
       or inverters can drive across a set of routing layers and  generates  a
       rule file for the repeaters

       For each repeater and routing layer a two pin net is created with given
       repeater  as  source  and  sink.  Based on timing, the distance between
       source and sink is automatically adjusted until slew  at  the  sink  is
       close  to the same as the input slew at the source. The command outputs
       a repeater rule file with one entry for each  specified  repeater  with
       the distance value that gives the least total delay among all slews and
       layers.  This  repeater  rule  file  can be used as an input to the re-
       peater-by-rule commands:  addRepeaterByRule

       Here is a sample rule file:
         SetBufferDrivingStrength <bufferName maxDistanceInMicrons maxCapLoad>
         SetBufferDrivingStrength ...
         SetDefaultDrivingStrength <maxDistanceInMicrons maxCapLoad>
         SetDistLastRepToSink <maxDistanceInMicrons>

       There is more information on repeater rule  syntax  here:  addRepeater-
       ByRule

Parameters
       -help  Prints  a  brief  description that includes the type and default
              information for each create_buffer_psPM_table parameter.  For  a
              detailed  description  of the command and all of its parameters,
              use the man command: man create_buffer_psPM_table

       -buffers <string>
              List of input buffers. Specified buffer should have only one in-
              put and one output.

              Data_type: string, optional

       -file <string>
              Specifies the addRepeaterByRule rule file name.

              Default: <designName>_repeater.rule.

              Data_type: string, optional

       -inverters <string>
              List of input inverters. Specified inverter should have only one
              input and one output.

              Data_type: string, optional

       -layer <string>
              Specifies the layer name.

              Default: All available routing layers.

              Data_type: string, optional

       -max_target_slew <float>
              Maximum target slew in picoseconds.

              Data_type: float, required

       -min_target_slew <float>
              Minimum target slew in picoseconds.

              Data_type: float, required

       -rpt_file <string>
              Report file name.

              Default: <designName>_buffer_psPM.rpt.

              Data_type: string, optional

       -slew_interval <float>
              Calculates the step and slew  range  interval.  Specified  value
              should be within [0.01 1.0].

              The step is calculated using the following:

              step = ($max_target_slew - $min_target_slew) * $slew_interval

              Default: 0.1

              Data_type: float, optional

Examples
              * The  following command reports distances and pico-second delay
                values per micron for specified buffers buf2 and  oabuf1  with
                given  minimum and maximum slews:

                create_buffer_psPM_table   -buffers  {buf2  oabuf1}  -max_tar-
                get_slew 100 -min_target_slew 70

              * The following command reports distance and  pico-second  delay
                values  per  micron  for specified buffers TBUFX1, TBUFX3, and
                TBUFX20 with given minimum, maximum slews, and slew interval:

                create_buffer_psPM_table  -buffers  {TBUFX1  TBUFX3   TBUFX20}
                -min_target_slew 90 -max_target_slew 120 -slew_interval 0.8

              * The  following command reports distances and pico-second delay
                values per micron for specified inverter CLKINVX8  with  given
                minimum, maximum slews, and slew interval:

                create_buffer_psPM_table  -inverters CLKINVX8 -min_target_slew
                70.0 -max_target_slew 80.0 -slew_interval 1.0

